25/11/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria shut down a 1,000mw nuclear unit after observing a steam leak, the Kozloduy nuclear power plant reported on Saturday (November 24). 
Plant authorities said the problem will be fixed within 48 hours, that radiation at the site remained unchanged and there was no threat to people living in the area. 
This was the second recent minor accident involving one of Kozloduy's two Soviet-built reactors. 
(DPA, BNT - 24/11//07)
